ntal asymptote at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y equals 3\"><math alttext=\"y equals 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the limit as x approaches, negative infinity, of, f of x, equals 3\"><math alttext=\"the limit as x approaches, negative infinity, of, f of x, equals 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><munder><mrow><mi>lim</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>∞</mi></mrow></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</li><li class=\"list_paragraph\">The graph of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f\"><math alttext=\"f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has a vertical asymptote at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals, negative 2 \"><math alttext=\"x equals, negative 2 \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mrow></math></span></span> because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the limit as x approaches, negative 2 from the right, of, f of x, equals negative infinity\"><math alttext=\"the limit as x approaches, negative 2 from the right, of, f of x, equals negative infinity\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><munder><mrow><mi>lim</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><msup><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>∞</mi></mrow></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</li></ol>\n",
